  "motivation": "Currently to create carousel or table of contents patterns authors can use ::scroll-marker pseudo elements to create navigation elements. As they are pseudo elements they have a number of limitations.\nThe scroll-target-group property allows to overcome such limitations by making HTML anchor elements 'scroll markers'. By specifying fragment identifier authors have 'scroll target into the view' functionality of ::scroll-markers, but don't have the 'tracking of current scroll marker' one. With scroll-target-group property, browser runs an algorithm to determine the 'current scroll marker' and authors can style such anchor element with :target-current pseudo class.",
